1939;;Everything Happens at Night;;American;;Irving Cummings;;Sonja Henie, Ray Milland, Robert Cummings;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everything_Happens_at_Night;;Ray Milland and Robert Cummings play competing newspaper reporters, in Switzerland, on the trail of the Nobel Prize winner Dr Norden. Norden was supposed to have been killed in Germany. Each reporter meets, and falls in love with, a young woman, played by Sonja Henie, who turns out to be Norden's daughter living under an assumed name. Their discovery of her father brings the Gestapo.